channel.title: Question about process()
channel.description: Ok so I'm still kind of new to coding, and I just wanted to see if I understand correctly. I have read in a few different places that deleting things from process() reduces lag. Is this true? I was going to delete pest control and fight pits anyways, but just wanted to know if it will make a difference with the amount of lag.

item.title: Question about process()
item.dc:creator: @kihomura Kihomura
item.description:
@kihomura wrote:

Basically process updates every 500 milliseconds, therefore putting something in there makes it update every 500 milliseconds, causing lag.

Read full topic

item.title: Question about process()
item.dc:creator: @jc22493 Jc22493
item.description:
@jc22493 wrote:

Yes, deleting stuff from process() will definitely reduce lag. Be careful not to delete any important parts.
